# Commit Message Template
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# <type>(<scope>): <summary>
#
# [Details]
# - Motivation and context
# - Changes or decisions
# - Breaking changes, if any
#
# [Refs: #issue-number]
#
# Examples:
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# feat(ui): support chat
# fix(security): check token expiry before redirect
# chore(scripts): add just script for common dev tasks
#
# Commit Types:
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# feat     - new feature
# fix      - bug fix
# docs     - documentation only
# style    - formatting, white-space, etc — no code change
# refactor - code restructure, no behavior change
# perf     - performance improvement
# test     - adding or fixing tests
# chore    - maintenance, tooling, setup, dependencies
#
# Commit Scopes:
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# Domain     → api, cli, ui, db, model, agent, data, security
# System     → env, build, ci, platform, scripts, lint, deps, release
# Project    → meta (README, LICENSE, .gitmessage etc.)
#
# Guidelines:
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Write a short, imperative summary in present tense.
# 2. Use a clear scope to indicate the module or concern.
# 3. Add detailed notes when helpful.
# 4. Link issues using: Refs: #issue
